The most recent two, a massive data theft in the German Bundestag and an email theft in the Democratic National Committee of the United States.
Cyber threats have affected our democratic process.
And there is a growing trend.
The more advanced computer technology is, the more vulnerable the means we use to protect our data.
In particular, a new computer technology, called quantum computers, uses the microscopic particles of nature to dramatically increase the computing power of computers.
Its computing power is powerful enough to crack many of the encryption systems we use today.
So are we hopeless?
